      "id": "11",
      "title": "पाण्याचे महत्त्व (Water)",
      "isLoaded": true,
      "summaryEn": "Water is the most precious natural resource and is essential for all life forms on Earth. Our bodies are made up of more than 60% water, highlighting its importance for our health. We need water not just for drinking but also for cleaning, cooking, and agriculture. Most of the Earth's surface is covered with water, but only a very small percentage of it is fresh and drinkable. Most water is found in oceans and is too salty for consumption. Fresh water is found in rivers, lakes, glaciers, and underground aquifers. Due to pollution and wastage, clean drinking water is becoming scarce in many parts of the world. Global warming is causing glaciers to melt too quickly, which disrupts the natural water cycle. We must practice water conservation by turning off taps when not in use and harvesting rainwater. Recycling water used for washing fruits to water plants is a great habit. Many farmers now use drip irrigation to save water in their fields. Large dams are built to store water for the whole year and generate electricity. However, we must ensure that industrial waste is not dumped into our clean rivers. Saving water today ensures that there will be enough for future generations. Public awareness programs help educate people about the dangers of water scarcity. World Water Day is celebrated on March 22nd to highlight the importance of fresh water. Let us all take a pledge to use water wisely and keep our water bodies clean. Every drop counts in the effort to save our planet.",
