      "summaryEn": "Animals are our companions and play a vital role in maintaining the balance of the ecosystem. There are millions of species of animals, ranging from tiny insects to giant whales. They are broadly classified into domestic and wild animals. Domestic animals like cows, sheep, and dogs provide us with milk, wool, and protection. Wild animals like lions, tigers, and elephants live in the jungle and help maintain the natural food chain. Animals possess remarkable senses, such as the keen eyesight of eagles or the acute hearing of owls. Some animals hibernate during winter, while others migrate long distances for food and weather. Many animals are threatened by habitat loss and poaching, leading to their possible extinction. National parks and wildlife sanctuaries are built to provide a safe home for endangered species. The tiger is India's national animal and represents strength and bravery. Birds like the peacock add beauty to our nature with their vibrant colors. Insects like bees are essential for pollination, which helps in the growth of crops and flowers. We must treat all animals with kindness and avoid hurting them for sport or fashion. Biodiversity is crucial because every animal, no matter how small, has a purpose in nature. Many people have pets at home, which can provide companionship and reduce stress. Learning about animals helps students appreciate the diversity of life on Earth. We should support conservation efforts to ensure that future generations can also see these majestic creatures. Let us remember that humans share this planet with animals and we must protect their rights. Protecting the animal kingdom is synonymous with protecting the health of our planet.",
